[The dire situation regarding the Japanese encephalitis outbreak in the
state of Uttar Pradesh (UP) does not seem to be improving at all. This is
readily seen by the fact that the death toll has increased by 200 in just
one week.
UP is situated in the north/northeast of India. UP and Nepal share a
considerable border for details). The patterns of this year's JE epidemic
in these 2 areas appear quite similar (for details see:
<http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/uttarpradesh/uttarpradeshlocation.htm> -
Mod.RY]
